  <section id="fs-id1909066">
    <title>Shell Filling and the Periodic Table</title>
    <para id="import-auto-id2616110"><link target-id="import-auto-id1526216"/> shows electron configurations for the first 20 elements in the periodic table, starting with hydrogen and its single electron and ending with calcium. The Pauli exclusion principle determines the maximum number of electrons allowed in each shell and subshell. But the order in which the shells and subshells are filled is complicated because of the large numbers of interactions between electrons.</para>


