    <exercise id="fs-id2378469" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2378470">
        <para id="import-auto-id2444200"><title>Integrated Concepts</title></para>
<para id="eip-id2588858">The electric and magnetic forces on an electron in the CRT in <link document="m42592" target-id="fs-id961353"/> are supposed to be in opposite directions. Verify this by determining the direction of each force for the situation shown. Explain how you obtain the directions (that is, identify the rules used).</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id3099218">
    <para id="import-auto-id3063565">The electric force on the electron is up (toward the positively charged plate). The magnetic force is down (by the RHR).</para>
