<para id="eip-id1616692">In a laboratory experiment designed to duplicate Thomson’s determination of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{q rSub { size 8{e} } /m rSub { size 8{e} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, a beam of electrons having a velocity of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>00</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>m/s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{6 "." "00" times "10" rSup { size 8{7} } `"m/s"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> enters a <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>5.00</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>T</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math> magnetic field. The beam moves perpendicular to the field in a path having a 6.80-cm radius of curvature. Determine <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math> from these observations, and compare the result with the known value.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id2519902">
